HEADWORD: Egg-bird
<hw>Egg"-bird`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>
<def>A species of tern, esp. the sooty tern (<spn>Sterna
fuliginosa</spn>) of the West Indies. In the Bahama Islands the name is
applied to the tropic bird, <spn>Pha⟦eum⟧thon
flavirostris</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

